#Docker Volumes

Today I learned about Docker volumes.

What is Volume:
Used to store data permanently outside container.

Command:

docker volume create myvolume

docker run -v myvolume:/data ubuntu

Learning:
Data inside container will not be lost even if container is deleted.


#Bind Mounts

Today I learned about bind mounts.

What is Bind Mount:
It links a folder from host machine to container.

Command:

docker run -v /host/path:/container/path ubuntu

Example:

docker run -v $(pwd):/app ubuntu

Learning:
I understood how to share files between system and container.
